1 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Definitions. (1) The definitions used in [sections 1 through 8] are for the
2 purpose of determining the eligibility of sites to receive and expend federal brownfields funding received by a
3 grant recipient from the United States environmental protection agency under the federal Brownfields
4 Revitalization and Environmental Restoration Act of 2001, Title II of Public Law 107-118.
5 (2) As used in [ sections 1 through 8] unless the context clearly indicates otherwise, the following
6 definitions apply:
7 (a) "Brownfield site" means an abandoned, idle, blighted, or underutilized property, for which the
8 expansion, redevelopment, or reuse of may be complicated by the presence or potential presence of hazardous
9 substances, pollutants, or contaminants.
10 (b) "Brownfields redevelopment" means any work or undertaking by a person to acquire a
11 brownfield site and to raze, demolish, remove, reconstruct, renovate, or rehabilitate the site or existing
12 buildings, structures, or other improvements at the site for the purpose of promoting the use of the site for
13 residential, commercial, industrial, or other purposes. The term does not include construction of new facilities
14 on the site for any purpose other than environmental remediation activities.
15 (c) "Department" means the department of environmental quality provided for in 2-15-3501.
16 (d) "Eligible entity" means a city, town, county, consolidated city-county, tribal government,
17 economic development organization, nonprofit organization, or state agency that has received federal
18 brownfields funding from the environmental protection agency or other state agency.
19 (e) "Environmental remediation activities" means:
20 (i) investigation, analysis, and monitoring of a brownfields site to determine the existence and
21 extent of actual or potential environmental pollution;
22 (ii) redevelopment planning; or
23 (iii) abatement, removal, or containment of environmental pollution at a brownfields site.
24 (f) "Hazardous substance" has the same meaning as provided in 75-10-602.
25 (g) "Petroleum" or "petroleum product" has the same meaning as provided in 75-11-302.
26 (h) "Petroleum tank release site" means a site where there has been a release from a petroleum
27 storage tank and assessment or remediation, or both, are being pursued in accordance with Title 75, chapter
28 11, part 3.
